  "body": "### Component\r\n\r\nForge\r\n\r\n### Describe the feature you would like\r\n\r\n# Current Behaviour\r\nWhen displaying method calls in the traces of forge tests / scripts currently the contract address is shortened to only show the first / last two bytes with the rest redacted / replaced by three dots:\r\ni.e.  `0xc02a...6cc2:withdraw` instead of `0xc02aaa39b223fe8d0a0e5c4f27ead9083c756cc2:withdraw`.\r\n\r\nAfaik there is no way to avoid this and this happens even at the highest verbosity level `-vvvvv`.\r\nThis makes it impossible to copy the addresses and paste it into a blockexplorer for example.\r\n\r\n# Proposed Behaviour\r\n\r\nWhen the user specifies the highest verbosity level `-vvvvv` show the full address without redaction. \r\n\r\nAlternatively add an additional argument `--show-full-addresses` to control this behaviour independently of the general verbosity setting.\r\n\r\n\r\n### Additional context\r\n\r\n_No response_",
